  "prompt": "What is meant by biology?",
  "response": "Biology is the scientific study of life and living organisms, including their physical structure, chemical processes, molecular interactions, physiological mechanisms, development, and evolution. It covers a wide range of topics and disciplines, from the study of single-celled organisms to the complex interactions of ecosystems. Biologists use various methods and techniques to understand the nature of living things, and their research has led to many important discoveries and advances in fields such as medicine, agriculture, and conservation.",
